@startuml
' This is a UML diagram showing the LunaSleep AI system architecture
' The diagram shows components, relationships, and data flow

title LunaSleep AI System Architecture

actor User

package "Frontend" {
  [Web Browser] as browser
  [Landing Page] as landing
  [Dashboard] as dashboard
  [Predictor] as predictor
  [Monitor] as monitor
  [AI Chat] as aichat
  [Authentication] as auth
}

package "Backend Services" {
  [Flask App] as flask
  [API Endpoints] as api
  [Authentication System] as authsys
  [ML Predictor] as ml
  [AI Assistant] as ai
  [Sensor Monitor] as sensor
}

package "Data Models" {
  [User Model] as usermodel
  [Prediction History] as predhist
  [Chat Sessions] as chatsess
  [Chat Messages] as chatmsg
}

database "Database" {
  [SQLite Database] as db
}

cloud "External Services" {
  [NVIDIA NIM API] as nim
  [XGBoost Model] as xgb
  [MPU6050 Sensor] as mpu6050
}

User --> browser
browser --> landing
browser --> dashboard
browser --> predictor
browser --> monitor
browser --> aichat
browser --> auth

landing --> flask
dashboard --> flask
predictor --> flask
monitor --> flask
aichat --> flask
auth --> flask

flask --> api
api --> authsys
api --> ml
api --> ai
api --> sensor

authsys --> usermodel
authsys --> predhist
authsys --> chatsess
authsys --> chatmsg

ml --> xgb
ai --> nim
sensor --> mpu6050

usermodel --> db
predhist --> db
chatsess --> db
chatmsg --> db

db --> usermodel
db --> predhist
db --> chatsess
db --> chatmsg

xgb --> ml
nim --> ai
mpu6050 --> sensor

note right of flask
Flask Application with:
- Flask-Login for authentication
- Flask-SQLAlchemy for database
- Flask-SocketIO for real-time monitoring
- HTMX for dynamic UI updates

note right of ml
XGBoost model for sleep efficiency prediction
Features:
- Age, Gender, Sleep duration
- REM/Deep/Light sleep %
- Awakenings, Caffeine/Alcohol consumption
- Smoking status, Exercise frequency

note right of ai
AI Assistant using NVIDIA NIM API
Features:
- Context-aware sleep coaching
- Personalized recommendations
- Chat session management

note right of sensor
Real-time sensor monitoring:
- MPU6050 accelerometer data
- Data simulation mode
- External sensor data support

note right of db
SQLite database storing:
- User authentication data
- Prediction history
- Chat conversations